{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-portfolio-template-js","path":"/signs-of-change/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Signs of Change","org":"National Taiwan University","year":2016,"coverImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/1ce68/img-13.jpg","srcSet":"/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/1f252/img-13.jpg 180w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/ef8fd/img-13.jpg 360w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/1ce68/img-13.jpg 720w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/6511a/img-13.jpg 1440w","sizes":"(min-width: 720px) 720px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/ff3fb/img-13.webp 180w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/ce5b5/img-13.webp 360w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/0f1b8/img-13.webp 720w,\n/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/c0ee5/img-13.webp 1440w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 720px) 720px, 100vw"}]},"width":720,"height":478}},"publicURL":"/static/9c2eedcb0ee2b6675f83e13a395255df/img-13.jpg"},"desc":"Designed Taiwan’s first identity for all-gender restrooms that highlights visually inclusive, emotionally safe, and publicly adaptable values."},"html":"<h1>Objective</h1>\n<p>Although Taiwan has been considered as one of the most progressive countries in gender equality in Asia, the oppression from the gender binary exists. Many of us are constantly putting ourselves and others in gender boxes that we just don’t fit into, whether or not we identify as transgender. In this case, there is a lack of all-gender restroom in university campuses as well as public spaces.</p>\n<p>In 2016, I was invited to develop the first visual identity system for all-gender restroom in Taiwan by the Campus Planning Office of National Taiwan University(NTU). Our all-gender Restroom Plan aims to offer safe and friendly spaces for toilet-using regardless the sexualities and gender identities of the users. We finally established the first installation guide for all gender restroom in Taiwan, which demonstrates the detailed to be concerned in order to reach a balance between safety, privacy, openness, comfortableness, reasonable budget and spatial efficiency.</p>\n<h1>My role</h1>\n<p>As a designer, I <strong>conducted the background research</strong>, <strong>organised the workshops for co-creating</strong> with the stakeholders, and designed the <strong>visual identity</strong> as well as the wayfinding system for the installation guide. I also votunteered in <strong>hosting some of the talks, designing the questionnaires, and reviewing the editorial content</strong>. I am very proud to be part of this project making some positive changes for more friendly public spaces.</p>\n<h1>Approach</h1>\n<h2>Participatory design process</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 23.333333333333332%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screenshot 2025-06-10 at 11.18.05 PM.png\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/29114/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/e85cb/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png 480w,\n/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/d9199/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png 960w,\n/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/29114/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png 1920w,\n/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/d9ed5/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png 2880w,\n/static/f6d744eea986ad9cb554f396a871f178/b6d22/Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png 2986w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>All gender restroom, needless to say, is a type of public facility so that we have to make it public from its beginning. It is crucial for designers to involve the participation of the stakeholders, especially the underrepresented disadvantaged groups, in shaping the design outcome for public spaces.</p>\n<p>I attended the executive team organised by the Campus Planning Office and Student Association of NTU. We held a series of speeches attended by over 400 audiences, 2 design workshops, and public hearing events before every restroom installation so as to collect the ideas about the design from the public. Moreover, the executive team is composed of heterogeneous members from different disciplines and backgrounds, which comprises the scholars specialising in gender issues, LGBTQIA rights activists, the student representatives, designers, architects and the manager of Campus Planning Office. In addtion, in general, the transgender and intersex people are not willing to show up in public events because of the pressure of coming-out, so we consulted some of them in person.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A workshop organised for collecting the ideas on the images used in the identity design, July, 2016\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/0f98f/img-03.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/7cc5e/img-03.jpg 480w,\n/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/6a068/img-03.jpg 960w,\n/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/0f98f/img-03.jpg 1920w,\n/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/eec88/img-03.jpg 2880w,\n/static/9083b1afb52a3cdb5e3f4ba72461aa7b/e6b01/img-03.jpg 3840w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>A workshop organised for collecting the ideas on the images used in the identity design, July, 2016</p>\n<h2>Design Concept</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-04.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3ea2d765ed3143554d045950ae3bb71f/0f98f/img-04.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3ea2d765ed3143554d045950ae3bb71f/7cc5e/img-04.jpg 480w,\n/static/3ea2d765ed3143554d045950ae3bb71f/6a068/img-04.jpg 960w,\n/static/3ea2d765ed3143554d045950ae3bb71f/0f98f/img-04.jpg 1920w,\n/static/3ea2d765ed3143554d045950ae3bb71f/e0c5a/img-04.jpg 2049w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>There are four primary elements in this design: <strong>Gender-neutral, Legibility, Emotionally Friendly, and Environmentally Adaptive.</strong></p>\n<h2>1. Gender-neutral</h2>\n<p>We avoided utilising the elements consolidating gender stereotypes such as smoking pipe, high-heeled shoes, and a female figure wearing skirt. Instead, we chose toilet and tap as the elements for design in order to imply some of the main functions of a restroom.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-05.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6fe70d63b30e1cdaf0c34df971aba043/0f98f/img-05.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6fe70d63b30e1cdaf0c34df971aba043/7cc5e/img-05.jpg 480w,\n/static/6fe70d63b30e1cdaf0c34df971aba043/6a068/img-05.jpg 960w,\n/static/6fe70d63b30e1cdaf0c34df971aba043/0f98f/img-05.jpg 1920w,\n/static/6fe70d63b30e1cdaf0c34df971aba043/e0c5a/img-05.jpg 2049w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>We hope that the primary colors would also be gender-neutral and have the cognitive connection with restroom. An elegant purple, which is made by combining red and blue, is the best choice. The reason is that red and blue are the most common colors used on restroom gender sign of female and male respectively.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-06.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/147cd2d93bdbc9754c7551f166614304/0f98f/img-06.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/147cd2d93bdbc9754c7551f166614304/7cc5e/img-06.jpg 480w,\n/static/147cd2d93bdbc9754c7551f166614304/6a068/img-06.jpg 960w,\n/static/147cd2d93bdbc9754c7551f166614304/0f98f/img-06.jpg 1920w,\n/static/147cd2d93bdbc9754c7551f166614304/e0c5a/img-06.jpg 2049w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>2. Legibility</h2>\n<p>The logo of “All Gender Restroom/ 性別友善廁所” is designed in a sans typeface, which is more legible than most of sans-serif and other decorative alternatives. The designated font for the related applications is Noto Traditional Chinese developed by Google, which is an open-source font with a good legibility and thus could be used by every sector without any doubt of infringement.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-07.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4784fa3d15e127480a0841e2d17af979/0f98f/img-07.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4784fa3d15e127480a0841e2d17af979/7cc5e/img-07.jpg 480w,\n/static/4784fa3d15e127480a0841e2d17af979/6a068/img-07.jpg 960w,\n/static/4784fa3d15e127480a0841e2d17af979/0f98f/img-07.jpg 1920w,\n/static/4784fa3d15e127480a0841e2d17af979/e0c5a/img-07.jpg 2049w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>3. Emotionally friendly</h2>\n<p>The logo and the extensive applications are designed with rounded edges in order to give the audiences an emotionally friendly impression, which indicates that this design an anti-oppression practice.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-08.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/dc452a0f705a2b6c1cfb0a06cec24f9c/0f98f/img-08.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dc452a0f705a2b6c1cfb0a06cec24f9c/7cc5e/img-08.jpg 480w,\n/static/dc452a0f705a2b6c1cfb0a06cec24f9c/6a068/img-08.jpg 960w,\n/static/dc452a0f705a2b6c1cfb0a06cec24f9c/0f98f/img-08.jpg 1920w,\n/static/dc452a0f705a2b6c1cfb0a06cec24f9c/e0c5a/img-08.jpg 2049w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>4. Environmentally adaptive</h2>\n<p>We released the design into the public domain within the full guide book for everyone who needs it, so it is necessary to take the concept “design after design” into consideration. For example, what kind of surrounding will the all gender restroom be installed with? It is impossible for us to know. Therefore, the best strategy is to make the design detailed but minimalist. It will maximise its adaptiveness.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-09.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e32a89655ccba8734e6e9926eaf6652c/0f98f/img-09.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e32a89655ccba8734e6e9926eaf6652c/7cc5e/img-09.jpg 480w,\n/static/e32a89655ccba8734e6e9926eaf6652c/6a068/img-09.jpg 960w,\n/static/e32a89655ccba8734e6e9926eaf6652c/0f98f/img-09.jpg 1920w,\n/static/e32a89655ccba8734e6e9926eaf6652c/3acf0/img-09.jpg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>The full guidelines and the original files was released in 2018.</p>\n<h1>Outcome</h1>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@imyentsen/installation-guide-for-all-gender-restroom-1182b6d7ee2d\">A full documentation of this work</a> (in English)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://homepage.ntu.edu.tw/~cpo/enactment/Handbook_for_All_Gender_Restroom_NTU.pdf\">The guidelines released by National Taiwan University</a> (in Mandarin)</li>\n<li>Media exposure of the work: <a href=\"https://hk.thenewslens.com/article/102699\">The New Lens</a> and <a href=\"https://womany.net/read/article/16597\">Womany</a> (both are in Mandarin).</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1771px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"cover.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c5b4a162fd00f64d3a844467cec94260/56b3a/cover.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c5b4a162fd00f64d3a844467cec94260/7cc5e/cover.jpg 480w,\n/static/c5b4a162fd00f64d3a844467cec94260/6a068/cover.jpg 960w,\n/static/c5b4a162fd00f64d3a844467cec94260/56b3a/cover.jpg 1771w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1771px) 100vw, 1771px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1786px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"unisex-restroom.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/35eb5e19b6b0936e679aab05a52b3448/5e0ab/unisex-restroom.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/35eb5e19b6b0936e679aab05a52b3448/7cc5e/unisex-restroom.jpg 480w,\n/static/35eb5e19b6b0936e679aab05a52b3448/6a068/unisex-restroom.jpg 960w,\n/static/35eb5e19b6b0936e679aab05a52b3448/5e0ab/unisex-restroom.jpg 1786w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1786px) 100vw, 1786px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-10.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/354cecb2a0a282678cf3edc5e8b3a855/0f98f/img-10.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/354cecb2a0a282678cf3edc5e8b3a855/7cc5e/img-10.jpg 480w,\n/static/354cecb2a0a282678cf3edc5e8b3a855/6a068/img-10.jpg 960w,\n/static/354cecb2a0a282678cf3edc5e8b3a855/0f98f/img-10.jpg 1920w,\n/static/354cecb2a0a282678cf3edc5e8b3a855/3acf0/img-10.jpg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-12.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b5e406d720d8a96f08363a7dff5eade9/0f98f/img-12.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b5e406d720d8a96f08363a7dff5eade9/7cc5e/img-12.jpg 480w,\n/static/b5e406d720d8a96f08363a7dff5eade9/6a068/img-12.jpg 960w,\n/static/b5e406d720d8a96f08363a7dff5eade9/0f98f/img-12.jpg 1920w,\n/static/b5e406d720d8a96f08363a7dff5eade9/3acf0/img-12.jpg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45833333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"img-11.jpg\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/0f98f/img-11.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/7cc5e/img-11.jpg 480w,\n/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/6a068/img-11.jpg 960w,\n/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/0f98f/img-11.jpg 1920w,\n/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/eec88/img-11.jpg 2880w,\n/static/bf9d0cac2c0e149dc91d10972e2d5de5/9ae6c/img-11.jpg 2934w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>","rawMarkdownBody":"\n\n# Objective\n\nAlthough Taiwan has been considered as one of the most progressive countries in gender equality in Asia, the oppression from the gender binary exists. Many of us are constantly putting ourselves and others in gender boxes that we just don’t fit into, whether or not we identify as transgender. In this case, there is a lack of all-gender restroom in university campuses as well as public spaces.\n\nIn 2016, I was invited to develop the first visual identity system for all-gender restroom in Taiwan by the Campus Planning Office of National Taiwan University(NTU). Our all-gender Restroom Plan aims to offer safe and friendly spaces for toilet-using regardless the sexualities and gender identities of the users. We finally established the first installation guide for all gender restroom in Taiwan, which demonstrates the detailed to be concerned in order to reach a balance between safety, privacy, openness, comfortableness, reasonable budget and spatial efficiency.\n\n# My role\n\nAs a designer, I **conducted the background research**, **organised the workshops for co-creating** with the stakeholders, and designed the **visual identity** as well as the wayfinding system for the installation guide. I also votunteered in **hosting some of the talks, designing the questionnaires, and reviewing the editorial content**. I am very proud to be part of this project making some positive changes for more friendly public spaces.\n\n# Approach\n\n## Participatory design process\n\n![Screenshot 2025-06-10 at 11.18.05 PM.png](./Screenshot_2025-06-10_at_11.18.05_PM.png)\n\nAll gender restroom, needless to say, is a type of public facility so that we have to make it public from its beginning. It is crucial for designers to involve the participation of the stakeholders, especially the underrepresented disadvantaged groups, in shaping the design outcome for public spaces.\n\nI attended the executive team organised by the Campus Planning Office and Student Association of NTU. We held a series of speeches attended by over 400 audiences, 2 design workshops, and public hearing events before every restroom installation so as to collect the ideas about the design from the public. Moreover, the executive team is composed of heterogeneous members from different disciplines and backgrounds, which comprises the scholars specialising in gender issues, LGBTQIA rights activists, the student representatives, designers, architects and the manager of Campus Planning Office. In addtion, in general, the transgender and intersex people are not willing to show up in public events because of the pressure of coming-out, so we consulted some of them in person.\n\n![A workshop organised for collecting the ideas on the images used in the identity design, July, 2016](./img-03.jpg)\n\nA workshop organised for collecting the ideas on the images used in the identity design, July, 2016\n\n## Design Concept\n\n![img-04.jpg](./img-04.jpg)\n\nThere are four primary elements in this design: **Gender-neutral, Legibility, Emotionally Friendly, and Environmentally Adaptive.**\n\n## 1. Gender-neutral\n\nWe avoided utilising the elements consolidating gender stereotypes such as smoking pipe, high-heeled shoes, and a female figure wearing skirt. Instead, we chose toilet and tap as the elements for design in order to imply some of the main functions of a restroom.\n\n![img-05.jpg](./img-05.jpg)\n\nWe hope that the primary colors would also be gender-neutral and have the cognitive connection with restroom. An elegant purple, which is made by combining red and blue, is the best choice. The reason is that red and blue are the most common colors used on restroom gender sign of female and male respectively.\n\n![img-06.jpg](./img-06.jpg)\n\n## 2. Legibility\n\nThe logo of “All Gender Restroom/ 性別友善廁所” is designed in a sans typeface, which is more legible than most of sans-serif and other decorative alternatives. The designated font for the related applications is Noto Traditional Chinese developed by Google, which is an open-source font with a good legibility and thus could be used by every sector without any doubt of infringement.\n\n![img-07.jpg](./img-07.jpg)\n\n## 3. Emotionally friendly\n\nThe logo and the extensive applications are designed with rounded edges in order to give the audiences an emotionally friendly impression, which indicates that this design an anti-oppression practice.\n\n![img-08.jpg](./img-08.jpg)\n\n## 4. Environmentally adaptive\n\nWe released the design into the public domain within the full guide book for everyone who needs it, so it is necessary to take the concept “design after design” into consideration. For example, what kind of surrounding will the all gender restroom be installed with? It is impossible for us to know. Therefore, the best strategy is to make the design detailed but minimalist. It will maximise its adaptiveness.\n\n![img-09.jpg](./img-09.jpg)\n\nThe full guidelines and the original files was released in 2018.\n\n# Outcome\n\n1. [A full documentation of this work](https://medium.com/@imyentsen/installation-guide-for-all-gender-restroom-1182b6d7ee2d) (in English)\n2. [The guidelines released by National Taiwan University](http://homepage.ntu.edu.tw/~cpo/enactment/Handbook_for_All_Gender_Restroom_NTU.pdf) (in Mandarin)\n3. Media exposure of the work: [The New Lens](https://hk.thenewslens.com/article/102699) and [Womany](https://womany.net/read/article/16597) (both are in Mandarin).\n\n![cover.jpg](./cover.jpg)\n\n![unisex-restroom.jpg](./unisex-restroom.jpg)\n\n![img-10.jpg](./img-10.jpg)\n\n![img-12.jpg](./img-12.jpg)\n\n![img-11.jpg](./img-11.jpg)"}},"pageContext":{"id":"96dde872-c8a7-59c5-9d30-a3b2a4e84468","previousPostId":"5f83a48a-e53b-5eff-9aac-5b0d7d33b819","nextPostId":"69e11be3-6001-5803-8a3a-39b74e914a63"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}